'''Max Kämper''' was a German [[Mining engineering|mining engineer]].
His 1908 survey and map of [[Mammoth Cave National Park|Mammoth Cave]], [[Kentucky]] represent the first accurate instrumental survey of portions of the cave system. Kämper arrived at Mammoth Cave in 1908 and left 8 months later in 1909.<ref>{{cite web|title=The German|url=http://www.nps.gov/maca/learn/historyculture/thegerman.htm|website=National Park Service|publisher=NPS|accessdate=January 30, 2016}}</ref>
Kämper was killed in trench warfare at the [[Somme River]] in north-eastern [[France]], on November&nbsp;10, 1916, during the closing days of the [[Battle of the Somme]]. He is buried in the War Cemetery of [[Cambrai]] near [[Arras, France|Arras]], [[France]].
